		(uuid "57468339-c467-496b-a9eb-9ac5be78aa31")
	)
	(text "I = 5mA"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 260.35 152.654 90)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
		)
		(uuid "6c443aa7-c38c-49a5-b9d2-6d5d9e5e66f7")
	)
	(text "Indictor circuit: \nThe ALERT pin as open drain. \nThe ALERT PIN gets grounded when ALERT is returned.\n\nALERT = ACTIVE = FLAG =>  ALERT PIN GROUNDED\nVGS > Vth \nGND - 5V > -0.6 => Q1 ON \n  \nALERT = INACTIVE =>  ALERT PIN FLOATS \nVGS > Vth\n+5 - +5 > -0.6 => Q1 OFF\n  \nALERT Digital output: Open-drain alert output, \ndefault state is active low - meaning floating when not asserted.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 184.404 -8.89 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "6cbf84ae-8f50-47bf-988a-62c62ceb362d")
	)
	(text "I2C BUS\nTHE PULL UPS ARE DETERMINED BY RISE TIME REQUIREMENTS.\nCBUS = CPCB + CMASTER + CSLAVE1 + CSLAVE2 + CSLAVE3...\n\nThe I2C standard specifies a max bus capacitance (CBUS MAX ) of 400 pF for both Standard Mode \nand Fast Mode and specifies 550 pF for Fast Mode Plus. This is not a lot of capacitance when \nconsidering the cumulative capacitance from PCB traces and the number of devices that can be \nsupported by the I2C interface, which has the ability to use multiple hundreds of device addresses. [SCPA054]\n\nMICROSTRIP CAPACITANCE: W = 0.3MM; 0.1 ABOVE GND \nUSUAL DEVICE CAPACITANCE: 10PF\n\nR_PULL CALC - VDD_MAX = 1.1 * 5  //+-10%\nRPU,MIN = (VDD_MAX-VOL_MAX)/(IOL) = (5*1.1-0.4)/3mA = 1K7 \n \nSTANDARD MODE- MAX: RISE TIME=1000NS, LINE 400PF:\nRPU,MAX = TR/(0.8473*CB) = 1000NS /(0.8473* 400P) = 3k [SLVA689]\n\nTHESE VALUES ARE PLOT IN TI SLVA689 FOR CONVENIENCE FIGURE 2. FIGURE 3\n\nEXCESS CAPACITANCE CAN BE SOLVED WITH BUFFERS"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -133.858 100.076 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "77de7253-1e44-4651-8c4c-467b10d7ac1c")
	)
	(text "The reason for selecting ina745 in spite of the fact that it is +-40A rated: \nThe chip is small pinned - only two pins to run.\nThe chip has got well defined and tested lsb for all the measured variables I/V/P/T. This will be very useful for evaluation. \nThe chip over its full scale offer still 1mA/LSB and 3.125mV/LSB\n\nIf we consider mesure for +-2.5A:\n2.5A/1mA = 2083.33 steps \n\nWhats more, this chip offer another methods like digital averaging and conversion time adjustment.\nThe other options that measure current over shunt, return voltage and would be fed into 16bits ADC. This would allow stretching the whole mV with gains over the full scale. \nConsequently the accuracy should be a bit better but it is questionable without testing in reference to particular design.\nThis sounds promising but would probably result into similar error over the whole pathway considering tolerances and layout and stm32 adc accuracy."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 299.212 97.028 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "866288a5-8609-462a-9dea-5154cafcf913")
	)
	(text "The voltage mesurements cannot be done with simple analogue current ics.\nthese will only provide good resolution but always will lead to voltage over the shunt. \nEven if the full scale is being covered. \nThe power monitoring IC use voltage divder in their packages. That is how the V is calculated. "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -134.366 74.168 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "ae4bffc8-5436-4229-a121-18e0b1e19aff")
	)
	(text "active low - mosfet is on - current is pulled loww"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 342.392 148.59 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "af161c42-b655-4fae-b10c-40ac292ab313")
	)
	(text "I = 5mA"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 205.74 120.904 90)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
		)
		(uuid "b7426cf4-ebad-4fe8-ba9c-450e0b8a5663")
	)
	(text "INA199 \nGBW: 80khz (gain 1), 30khz (gain 2), 14khz (gain 3) \n\nfor small power dissipation, r_shunt needs to be small, this produces small voltage drop over it. \nTo fit the adc scale on STM32 - 3V3 - assuming V = 0.008ohms * 2.5A, maximum gain would have to be used. -Bandwidth 14khz. "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -134.112 60.452 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "ccfbd9ca-4fe5-44ba-a1f1-7657266c36e1")
	)
